<br>
Rogue only needs 200 LP skill. Can do it at level 40 np. Goo's see through Sneak and Hide so make a puller hotkey to rogue. Rogue stands at door and keeps it open. Monk needs SOW and not SOE. When pulling from elevator, Rogues goes in, clicks elevator, monk goes up, rogue brings elevator down, and heads back to first door.<br>
<br>
The Mob that pops from the bottom reavers is Lord Rak Ashiir. He is the final fight for the Shaman Epic and requires the turn in of a tear from the Plane of Fear.<br>
<br>
Have the monk pull the reavers out of the building and off to one side. The monk FD's at the corner and you wait for mobs to start leaving. If your warrior is 57+ or 58+ (I forget which level) they can single pull a reaver out of a crowd of mobs. Otherwise, you need to have the monk get fancy and get up FD get up FD to make the reaver stay, or mez any adds.<br>
<br>
Make sure that people wait for assist, as you can lose agro when blind if you are pushed away from the reaver. Have people wait for assist after every split as well. If you can two box the MA to see what is going on when blind, that helps a lot.<br>
<br>
Just go slowly and pick a good Puller. The puller can make all the difference. Having a Warrior able to single pull the reavers out of a crowd is huge. I have 9 epic druids in my guild. I spent a LOT of time in CoM <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
